1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:02,279
My name is Talal Mustafa al-Shuweimi

2
00:00:02,439 --> 00:00:05,599
I’m from Raqqa Province, living on Sajiyah Street

3
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:09,359
I’m 45 years old

4
00:00:11,599 --> 00:00:15,800
I have 3 wives and 13 children

5
00:00:19,559 --> 00:00:24,320
During the Assad regime’s control of Raqqa, I worked at the Water Department

6
00:00:25,239 --> 00:00:27,800
After the problems and battles started

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,280
I was dismissed from work

8
00:00:32,679 --> 00:00:35,200
The regime accused me of being a terrorist

9
00:00:35,719 --> 00:00:38,320
The Air Force Intelligence raided my house

10
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,359
Because they claimed I was a terrorist

11
00:00:40,799 --> 00:00:42,359
The dismissal order came from Damascus

12
00:00:42,359 --> 00:00:43,359
Of course

13
00:00:43,679 --> 00:00:45,719
It was all a malicious report

14
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:49,240
Because we were locals and stayed in the city

15
00:00:50,799 --> 00:00:54,000
My dismissal order came in 2012

16
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:57,479
So I fled Raqqa for a while

17
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,759
And my brother was arrested

18
00:00:59,439 --> 00:01:00,679
By the Assad regime

19
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:02,840
On behalf of the regime

20
00:01:03,159 --> 00:01:07,519
They put him in Sednaya Prison for about 6 years

21
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:14,719
After they detained my brother for 6 years in prison

22
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,040
The Free Syrian Army entered Raqqa

23
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:21,680
I was already dismissed from work as a “terrorist”

24
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:24,920
About 6 or 7 months after the FSA entered

25
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:30,040
ISIS entered the city, calling itself the Islamic State

26
00:01:31,079 --> 00:01:33,519
They took control of the area

27
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:37,560
Within their first 2 or 3 months of settling in

28
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:43,000
They arrested me, accusing me of being a regime agent,a <i>shabiha</i> [pro-regime thug]

29
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:50,920
They detained me at Point 11, with the security members

30
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:53,319
Inside the former Governor’s Palace

31
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,599
I stayed there for about a week

32
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,560
After the Governor’s Palace, they took me

33
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:04,319
To a new security base near the National Hospital area in Raqqa

34
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:07,519
It was inside the old Military Judiciary building of the Assad regime

35
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:13,000
A week later, they moved me from the Governor’s Palace basement

36
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:17,240
To the old Military Judiciary building near the Traffic Circle

37
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,400
I stayed in that base

38
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:22,000
Under the same charge, regime agent

39
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,400
I stayed there for 53 days

40
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,120
After 53 days

41
00:02:27,319 --> 00:02:30,319
They released me because there was no evidence against me

42
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,800
The one who interrogated me

43
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,319
Was from Raqqa Province, from Tabqa city

44
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,520
His family name was Khameesi

45
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,919
He was called Abu Yousuf, the interrogator

46
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:43,360
He was the head of interrogators

47
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:47,400
Another man was nicknamed Abu Abdurrahman

48
00:02:48,759 --> 00:02:51,879
His name was Mahmoud al-Ali al-Sahou from the Ghanem al-Zahir clan

49
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,719
From an area called al-Jaif

50
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:57,120
East of the al-Eywij area

51
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,520
Near Rashid Farm in Raqqa

52
00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:05,039
I stayed under interrogation for about 53 days

53
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:08,960
After they confirmed there was nothing against me

54
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:12,479
They realized I’d already been dismissed by the Assad regime as a “terrorist”

55
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,080
So they released me

56
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,800
And gave me a clearance card

57
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,280
A certificate proving there were no charges against me

58
00:03:20,319 --> 00:03:24,319
As a Syrian citizen

59
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:25,639
And a Sunni by faith

60
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:28,879
I went back to work with the other workers

61
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,439
Trying to earn a living to support my children

62
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,319
Around 50 or 60 days after returning

63
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:39,159
I was surprised to see someone

64
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:45,199
Sadly, he was from the same neighborhood, Sunni, and a local of the area

65
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:47,800
His name was Mahmoud al-Shahada

66
00:03:48,879 --> 00:03:50,680
He was an ISIS emir overseeing the Water Department

67
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,000
His name was Mahmoud al-Shahada

68
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:53,719
Known as Abu Hudhayfa

69
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:57,680
Abu Hudhayfa had been detained in Assad regime prisons back in 2000

70
00:03:57,719 --> 00:03:59,120
Accused of joining Jund al-Sham

71
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:04,080
He struck a deal with the regime in Sednaya Prison and was released

72
00:04:04,199 --> 00:04:08,120
Then brought to Raqqa and appointed as an emir in the caliphate

73
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:14,840
Mahmoud al-Shahada, known as Abu Hudhayfa, and his brother were both active and skilled

74
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,639
His brother’s name was Hassan

75
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,839
He had two brothers, Hassan and Hassaan

76
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:21,600
His brother was an emir and his right-hand man

77
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:24,480
When I came back to the Water Department

78
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:29,720
I was surprised he’d become the department’s emir after being released from Sednaya

79
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:33,360
When the workers learned I was coming to work again

80
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:37,879
I had no salary, but people gave us charity for the children

81
00:04:38,079 --> 00:04:41,279
They offered us odd jobs outside

82
00:04:41,279 --> 00:04:45,199
Of course, we had no fixed income since I and others were dismissed from work

83
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,519
Then Abu Hudhayfa came

84
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,800
And arrested me himself,Mahmoud al-Shahada

85
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,920
By then, he’d become “Minister of the Caliphate” because of his influence and knowledge

86
00:04:58,439 --> 00:05:01,000
He had many initiatives, so he arrested me

87
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,720
He tricked me into it

88
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:07,319
At the time, we were fixing a broken water line

89
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,120
In the Khasra Faraj area, and when we came

90
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,480
He said, “The sheikh wants to see you”

91
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:19,839
“He wants to ask a few questions, and there’s also a broken pipe at the security point”

92
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,879
He said, “You should fix it.” I said, “As you wish, Abu Hudhayfa”

93
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:31,519
When I arrived there, I only saw weapons pointed at me

94
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:35,040
They threw me to the ground, stepped on my neck, and arrested me

95
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:36,920
For about two months

96
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,920
When I returned to work at the Water Department

97
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,519
Abu Hudhayfa grabbed me by the hair

98
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:44,240
Dragged me toward the table

99
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,120
Pressed my head onto it

100
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:49,279
And placed his foot on my left shoulder

101
00:05:49,879 --> 00:05:54,000
He said to me, “You’re a shabih (pro-regime thug). You shouldn’t enter the institution. You’re an agent for the regime”

102
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:59,519
I told him, Calm down, Sheikh, this is my clearance from Point 11, and I’m clean, there’s nothing against me

103
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:02,079
I have children, but he said, No, you’re a shabih

104
00:06:02,639 --> 00:06:04,800
And no one will be able to get you back to work

105
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:10,600
We brought mediations from one sheikh and another, but nothing worked

106
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:13,759
At that point, I had a small amount of money

107
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:16,279
And my brother had about 125,000 Syrian pounds

108
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,160
So I bought a taxi

109
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:20,360
A taxi with no official papers

110
00:06:20,399 --> 00:06:23,120
Back then they used to call it “<i>Arouriya</i>”

111
00:06:33,254 --> 00:06:37,435
Because it was stolen,they’d steal and sell it without papers

112
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,319
So they called it an “<i>Arouriya</i> car”

113
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:33,560
I worked as a taxi driver

114
00:06:34,319 --> 00:06:36,439
For about 5 to 6 months

115
00:06:37,399 --> 00:06:39,240
One day

116
00:06:41,759 --> 00:06:44,079
The Hisba (religious police) raided me at my home

117
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,600
On 16th Street

118
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:53,000
They said to me, You’re a man who trades cigarettes

119
00:06:53,639 --> 00:06:55,720
And they detained me for 4 days

120
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:03,000
They insulted me, but it wasn’t severe or extreme

121
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,600
They kept saying, You’re a cigarette dealer, and so on

122
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:11,480
I told him, Sheikh, I’m not a cigarette dealer, I don’t even smoke cigarettes, but yes, I smoke hookah

123
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:13,600
Yes, I smoke hookah

124
00:07:14,439 --> 00:07:18,120
But I don’t smoke cigarettes. If I did, I’d tell you

125
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,079
Anyway, they detained me

126
00:07:20,759 --> 00:07:21,759
One man

127
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:25,199
And took me to a Hisba base called “Panorama”

128
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:29,199
It’s in Raqqa, near Maqs Roundabout, called “Panorama”

129
00:07:29,639 --> 00:07:32,399
There was a Hisba base there. The emir in charge was Abu Bishr

130
00:07:32,439 --> 00:07:34,040
Abu Bishr, a Saudi national

131
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,120
After 4 days of detention

132
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:43,160
I moved my home to another neighborhood, fearing someone was targeting me

133
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:47,720
I was hungry, and I had 12 or 13 children

134
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,279
There was no strength left in me

135
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:56,000
I thought, There are people who trade cigarettes and make a living from it

136
00:07:56,759 --> 00:08:00,680
So I started selling cigarettes. Honestly, the accusation already stuck to me anyway

137
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:03,959
So I decided to trade cigarettes

138
00:08:04,879 --> 00:08:06,240
And I began working in that trade

139
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:09,040
For about a month or a month and a half

140
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:12,920
Then a Hisba patrol came and arrested me

141
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,360
They detained me for about 15 days

142
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,800
And the one who arrested me

143
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:25,439
Was a man from Rumaila named Mustafa al-Hamid al-Muslih

144
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,839
Known as Abu Seif Maqs

145
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:31,240
He also had another nom de guerre, Abu Seif Doshka

146
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,679
Also known as Abu Seif Maqs

147
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:37,399
He was originally from the Wahb clan

148
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:41,200
His maternal uncles were from the Masaar group of the Barij clan

149
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,480
As for Abu Seif Maqs, his past

150
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,919
Was extremely bad

151
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:52,000
He used to take hashish and pills and was unemployed

152
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:55,440
And strangely enough

153
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:59,759
When ISIS entered, I was shocked to see he had become a Doshka gunner

154
00:08:59,799 --> 00:09:02,919
Then, since he was from the area and knew people

155
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:06,799
They made him emir of the Search and Investigation Unit, this man called Mustafa

156
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:09,600
Mustafa arrested me

157
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:14,519
For the second time, for about 15 days. He tortured, beat, and insulted me

158
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:16,720
Of course, they found no cigarettes with me

159
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:22,759
The emir of the Search Unit was the same Mustafa al-Muslih

160
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,720
Known as Abu Seif

161
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:29,639
And another man called Ibrahim al-Ali al-Khayheet

162
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:34,399
From the Ghanem al-Zahir clan, living near the Jazra Junction in Raqqa

163
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,720
Known as Abu Hudhayfa

164
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:40,919
Abu Hudhayfa was about 30 years old

165
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:45,039
The sharia official was Abu Hamza al-Tunsi

166
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:49,320
There was another man, originally from Sukhna, living on Sajiyah Street in Raqqa

167
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,600
Named Abu Zayd

168
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,759
His brother was the emir of the Islamic Police

169
00:09:53,919 --> 00:09:56,759
In Raqqa Province, overseeing the whole wilaya

170
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,679
Abu Zayd was a sharia official

171
00:09:58,759 --> 00:10:02,039
Second in rank under Abu Hamza al-Tunsi

172
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:07,960
He worked as a messenger between the court and the Hisba’s sharia office

173
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,559
As for how many times I was imprisoned

174
00:10:11,559 --> 00:10:17,399
If I tried to describe my suffering, I’d need 3 months to finish

175
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:21,120
The torture and misery we endured

176
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:24,840
I was imprisoned 28 times

177
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:28,799
Some people might think I’m lying, but the locals know me well

178
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:33,200
My bag was always ready, because every 2 or 3 days ISIS would arrest me

179
00:10:33,639 --> 00:10:37,399
The first time I was jailed in a security checkpoint, the charge was suspicion

180
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:40,159
I was imprisoned there for 56 days

181
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:45,720
The other 27 times were all for cigarette trading

182
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:50,759
My detentions ranged between 10 to 15 days, sometimes up to 2 months

183
00:10:50,919 --> 00:10:55,879
Then they’d release me, since they found no evidence, and I was very cautious around them
